</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs" id="cell-id=8MlIWaYFDNVq">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [245]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># define the parameters of the tree to iterate over</span>
<span class="n">max_depth_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">11</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">max_leaf_nodes_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">51</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">min_samples_split_values</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">np</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">arange</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">51</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># initialize variables to store the best model and its performance</span>
<span class="n">best_estimator</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="kc">None</span>
<span class="n">best_score_diff</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">float</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">'inf'</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># iterate over all combinations of the specified parameter values</span>
<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">max_depth</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">max_depth_values</span><span class="p">:</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">max_leaf_nodes</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">max_leaf_nodes_values</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">min_samples_split</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">min_samples_split_values</span><span class="p">:</span>

            <span class="c1"># initialize the tree with the current set of parameters</span>
            <span class="n">estimator</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DecisionTreeClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span>
                <span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="p">,</span>
                <span class="n">max_leaf_nodes</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">max_leaf_nodes</span><span class="p">,</span>
                <span class="n">min_samples_split</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">min_samples_split</span><span class="p">,</span>
                <span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">42</span>
            <span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="c1"># fit the model to the training data</span>
            <span class="n">estimator</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="c1"># make predictions on the training and test sets</span>
            <span class="n">y_train_pred</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">estimator</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="n">y_test_pred</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">estimator</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_test</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="c1"># calculate F1 scores for training and test sets</span>
            <span class="n">train_f1_score</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">f1_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train_pred</span><span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="n">test_f1_score</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">f1_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_test</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_test_pred</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="c1"># calculate the absolute difference between training and test F1 scores</span>
            <span class="n">score_diff</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">abs</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">train_f1_score</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="n">test_f1_score</span><span class="p">)</span>

            <span class="c1"># update the best estimator and best score if the current one has a smaller score difference</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">score_diff</span> <span class="o">&lt;</span> <span class="n">best_score_diff</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="n">best_score_diff</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">score_diff</span>
                <span class="n">best_estimator</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">estimator</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=9cAQmi97Dqbv">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [246]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># creating an instance of the best model</span>
<span class="n">dtree2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">best_estimator</span>

<span class="c1"># fitting the best model to the training data</span>
<span class="n">dtree2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>

  /* Definition of color scheme common for light and dark mode */
  --sklearn-color-text: #000;
  --sklearn-color-text-muted: #666;
  --sklearn-color-line: gray;
  /* Definition of color scheme for unfitted estimators */
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0: #fff5e6;
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1: #f6e4d2;
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2: #ffe0b3;
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3: chocolate;
  /* Definition of color scheme for fitted estimators */
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-0: #f0f8ff;
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-1: #d4ebff;
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-2: #b3dbfd;
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-3: cornflowerblue;

  /* Specific color for light theme */
  --sklearn-color-text-on-default-background: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));
  --sklearn-color-background: var(--sg-background-color, var(--theme-background, var(--jp-layout-color0, white)));
  --sklearn-color-border-box: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));

#sk-container-id-25 div.sk-container {
  /* jupyter's `normalize.less` sets `[hidden] { display: none; }`
     but bootstrap.min.css set `[hidden] { display: none !important; }`
     so we also need the `!important` here to be able to override the
     default hidden behavior on the sphinx rendered scikit-learn.org.
     See: https://github.com/scikit-learn/scikit-learn/issues/21755 */
  display: inline-block !important;
  position: relative;
}

#sk-container-id-25 div.sk-text-repr-fallback {
  display: none;
}

div.sk-serial,
div.sk-item {

  background-image: linear-gradient(var(--sklearn-color-text-on-default-background), var(--sklearn-color-text-on-default-background));

/* Toggleable style: style used for estimator/Pipeline/ColumnTransformer box that is
clickable and can be expanded/collapsed.
- Pipeline and ColumnTransformer use this feature and define the default style
- Estimators will overwrite some part of the style using the `sk-estimator` class
*/

/* Pipeline and ColumnTransformer style (default) */

#sk-container-id-25 div.sk-toggleable {
  /* Default theme specific background. It is overwritten whether we have a
  specific estimator or a Pipeline/ColumnTransformer */
  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);
}

/* Toggleable label */
#sk-container-id-25 label.sk-toggleable__label {
  cursor: pointer;
  display: flex;
  width: 100%;
  margin-bottom: 0;
  padding: 0.5em;

  align-items: start;

  gap: 0.5em;
}

}

  /* Arrow on the left of the label */
  content: "▸";
  float: left;
  margin-right: 0.25em;
  color: var(--sklearn-color-icon);
}

  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);
}

  max-height: 0;
  max-width: 0;
  overflow: hidden;
  text-align: left;

}

}

  /* unfitted */

  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-0);

  /* Expand drop-down */
  max-height: 200px;
  max-width: 100%;
  overflow: auto;

  content: "▾";
}

/* Pipeline/ColumnTransformer-specific style */

#sk-container-id-25 div.sk-label input.sk-toggleable__control:checked~label.sk-toggleable__label {
  color: var(--sklearn-color-text);
  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2);
}

  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-fitted-level-2);

<script>
      const buttonEl =
        document.querySelector('#df-0f99440b-911d-4bd3-ad4b-7e57c5de112a button.colab-df-convert');
      buttonEl.style.display =
        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';

      async function convertToInteractive(key) {
        const element = document.querySelector('#df-0f99440b-911d-4bd3-ad4b-7e57c5de112a');
        const dataTable =
          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',
                                                    [key], {});
        if (!dataTable) return;

        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +
          '<a target="_blank" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'
          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';
        element.innerHTML = '';
        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';
        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);
        const docLink = document.createElement('div');
        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;
        element.appendChild(docLink);
      }
    </script>

<script>
      const buttonEl =
        document.querySelector('#df-df182c02-e90e-43ca-aa38-26e5c54ab8dc button.colab-df-convert');
      buttonEl.style.display =
        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';

      async function convertToInteractive(key) {
        const element = document.querySelector('#df-df182c02-e90e-43ca-aa38-26e5c54ab8dc');
        const dataTable =
          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',
                                                    [key], {});
        if (!dataTable) return;

        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +
          '<a target="_blank" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'
          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';
        element.innerHTML = '';
        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';
        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);
        const docLink = document.createElement('div');
        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;
        element.appendChild(docLink);
      }
    </script>
</div>

<li>There is a difference between the training and test F1 Scores.This indicates that the model is overfitting.</li>

<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="n">rf_estimator_train_perf</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">model_performance_classification_sklearn</span><span class="p">(</span>

</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<ul>
<li>There is a difference between the training and test F1 Scores.This indicates that the model is overfitting.</li>
<li>Not hypertuning this intentionally now as the best three models will be hypertuned later in the section. Hence we will now consider Ada Boost</li>
</ul>

  align-self: flex-start;
  width: 50%;

  width: 0;

/* Toggleable style: style used for estimator/Pipeline/ColumnTransformer box that is
clickable and can be expanded/collapsed.
- Pipeline and ColumnTransformer use this feature and define the default style
- Estimators will overwrite some part of the style using the `sk-estimator` class
*/

/* Pipeline and ColumnTransformer style (default) */

#sk-container-id-27 div.sk-toggleable {
  /* Default theme specific background. It is overwritten whether we have a
  specific estimator or a Pipeline/ColumnTransformer */
  background-color: var(--sklearn-color-background);
}

<script>
      const buttonEl =
        document.querySelector('#df-f58b9754-acc7-4e9c-8296-cda062ba824d button.colab-df-convert');
      buttonEl.style.display =
        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';

      async function convertToInteractive(key) {
        const element = document.querySelector('#df-f58b9754-acc7-4e9c-8296-cda062ba824d');
        const dataTable =
          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',
                                                    [key], {});
        if (!dataTable) return;

        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +
          '<a target="_blank" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'
          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';
        element.innerHTML = '';
        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';
        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);
        const docLink = document.createElement('div');
        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;
        element.appendChild(docLink);
      }
    </script>

<script>
      const buttonEl =
        document.querySelector('#df-e9725780-5e34-47d7-8559-5a677f75bdc6 button.colab-df-convert');
      buttonEl.style.display =
        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';

      async function convertToInteractive(key) {
        const element = document.querySelector('#df-e9725780-5e34-47d7-8559-5a677f75bdc6');
        const dataTable =
          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',
                                                    [key], {});
        if (!dataTable) return;

        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +
          '<a target="_blank" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'
          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';
        element.innerHTML = '';
        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';
        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);
        const docLink = document.createElement('div');
        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;
        element.appendChild(docLink);
      }
    </script>
</div>

<ul>
<li>Compare to others so far the train and test is almost similar. There is a slight difference between the training and test F1 Scores.This indicates that the model is slightly overfitting.</li>
<li>Not hypertuning this intentionally now as the best three models will be hypertuned later in the section. Hence we will now consider Gradient Boost</li>
</ul>

          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';

</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<ul>
<li>As with AdaBoosting there is a slight difference between the training and test F1 Scores.This indicates that the model is slightly overfitting.</li>
<li>Not hypertuning this intentionally now as the best three models will be hypertuned later in the section. Hence we will now consider XG Boost</li>
</ul>

<style>#sk-container-id-29 {
  /* Definition of color scheme common for light and dark mode */
  --sklearn-color-text: #000;
  --sklearn-color-text-muted: #666;
  --sklearn-color-line: gray;
  /* Definition of color scheme for unfitted estimators */
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-0: #fff5e6;
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-1: #f6e4d2;
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-2: #ffe0b3;
  --sklearn-color-unfitted-level-3: chocolate;
  /* Definition of color scheme for fitted estimators */
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-0: #f0f8ff;
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-1: #d4ebff;
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-2: #b3dbfd;
  --sklearn-color-fitted-level-3: cornflowerblue;

  /* Specific color for light theme */
  --sklearn-color-text-on-default-background: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));
  --sklearn-color-background: var(--sg-background-color, var(--theme-background, var(--jp-layout-color0, white)));
  --sklearn-color-border-box: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, black)));
  --sklearn-color-icon: #696969;

  @media (prefers-color-scheme: dark) {
    /* Redefinition of color scheme for dark theme */
    --sklearn-color-text-on-default-background: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, white)));
    --sklearn-color-background: var(--sg-background-color, var(--theme-background, var(--jp-layout-color0, #111)));
    --sklearn-color-border-box: var(--sg-text-color, var(--theme-code-foreground, var(--jp-content-font-color1, white)));
    --sklearn-color-icon: #878787;
  }
}

<script>
      const buttonEl =
        document.querySelector('#df-cdd6c97f-b53b-4045-a395-37a8c7820bdc button.colab-df-convert');
      buttonEl.style.display =
        google.colab.kernel.accessAllowed ? 'block' : 'none';

      async function convertToInteractive(key) {
        const element = document.querySelector('#df-cdd6c97f-b53b-4045-a395-37a8c7820bdc');
        const dataTable =
          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',
                                                    [key], {});
        if (!dataTable) return;

        const docLinkHtml = 'Like what you see? Visit the ' +
          '<a target="_blank" href=https://colab.research.google.com/notebooks/data_table.ipynb>data table notebook</a>'
          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';
        element.innerHTML = '';
        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';
        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);
        const docLink = document.createElement('div');
        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;
        element.appendChild(docLink);
      }
    </script>
</div>

        const element = document.querySelector('#df-461062d3-397d-4deb-9957-eb3e7eb2a07c');
        const dataTable =
          await google.colab.kernel.invokeFunction('convertToInteractive',
                                                    [key], {});

          + ' to learn more about interactive tables.';
        element.innerHTML = '';
        dataTable['output_type'] = 'display_data';
        await google.colab.output.renderOutput(dataTable, element);

        docLink.innerHTML = docLinkHtml;

<h4 id="Before-we-under-or-over-sample-the-data,-let-us-split-the-data-into-train,-test-and-validation">Before we under or over sample the data, let us split the data into train, test and validation<a class="anchor-link" href="#Before-we-under-or-over-sample-the-data,-let-us-split-the-data-into-train,-test-and-validation">¶</a></h4>
</div>
</div>

</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=pGvQ4vACXkb5">

<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Splitting data into training, validation and test set:</span>

<span class="c1"># first we split data into 2 parts, say temporary and test</span>
<span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X_temp</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_temp</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">train_test_split</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">X</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">test_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">stratify</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">y</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># then we split the temporary set into train and validation</span>
<span class="n">X_val</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X_test</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_val</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_test</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">train_test_split</span><span class="p">(</span>
    <span class="n">X_temp</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_temp</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">test_size</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">0.4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">stratify</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">y_temp</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shape</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X_val</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shape</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">X_test</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">shape</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>

<li>Oversampling the data using SMOTE</li>

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [278]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Fit SMOTE on train data(Synthetic Minority Oversampling Technique)</span>
<span class="n">sm</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">SMOTE</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">sampling_strategy</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="s1">'auto'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">k_neighbors</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">X_train_over</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train_over</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">sm</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit_resample</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Predicting the target for train and validation set</span>
<span class="n">pred_train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dtree2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train_over</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">pred_val</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dtree2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_val</span><span class="p">)</span>

</style><div class="sk-top-container" id="sk-container-id-31"><div class="sk-text-repr-fallback"><pre>BaggingClassifier(random_state=1)</pre><b>In a Jupyter environment, please rerun this cell to show the HTML representation or trust the notebook. <br/>On GitHub, the HTML representation is unable to render, please try loading this page with nbviewer.org.</b></div><div class="sk-container" hidden=""><div class="sk-item"><div class="sk-estimator fitted sk-toggleable"><input checked="" class="sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually" id="sk-estimator-id-33" type="checkbox"/><label class="sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow" for="sk-estimator-id-33"><div><div>BaggingClassifier</div></div><div><a class="sk-estimator-doc-link fitted" href="https://scikit-learn.org/1.6/modules/generated/sklearn.ensemble.BaggingClassifier.html" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">?<span>Documentation for BaggingClassifier</span></a><span class="sk-estimator-doc-link fitted">i<span>Fitted</span></span></div></label><div class="sk-toggleable__content fitted"><pre>BaggingClassifier(random_state=1)</pre></div> </div></div></div></div>

<h3 id="Model-Building-with-undersampled-data">Model Building with undersampled data<a class="anchor-link" href="#Model-Building-with-undersampled-data">¶</a></h3>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell jp-mod-noOutputs" id="cell-id=0xsmooeCtqkt">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [310]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># fit random under sampler on the train data</span>
<span class="n">rus</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">RandomUnderSampler</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">sampling_strategy</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="n">X_train_un</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train_un</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">rus</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit_resample</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<span class="n">pred_train</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">dtree2</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train_un</span><span class="p">)</span>

<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Checking recall score on undersampled train and validation set</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">recall_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_train_un</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pred_train</span><span class="p">))</span>

</style><div class="sk-top-container" id="sk-container-id-37"><div class="sk-text-repr-fallback"><pre>BaggingClassifier(random_state=1)</pre><b>In a Jupyter environment, please rerun this cell to show the HTML representation or trust the notebook. <br/>On GitHub, the HTML representation is unable to render, please try loading this page with nbviewer.org.</b></div><div class="sk-container" hidden=""><div class="sk-item"><div class="sk-estimator fitted sk-toggleable"><input checked="" class="sk-toggleable__control sk-hidden--visually" id="sk-estimator-id-39" type="checkbox"/><label class="sk-toggleable__label fitted sk-toggleable__label-arrow" for="sk-estimator-id-39"><div><div>BaggingClassifier</div></div><div><a class="sk-estimator-doc-link fitted" href="https://scikit-learn.org/1.6/modules/generated/sklearn.ensemble.BaggingClassifier.html" rel="noreferrer" target="_blank">?<span>Documentation for BaggingClassifier</span></a><span class="sk-estimator-doc-link fitted">i<span>Fitted</span></span></div></label><div class="sk-toggleable__content fitted"><pre>BaggingClassifier(random_state=1)</pre></div> </div></div></div></div>

<h2 id="Model-Performances">Model Performances<a class="anchor-link" href="#Model-Performances">¶</a></h2>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=mUR38mCsUUVG">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Based on the recall data on the train and validation scores below is the data</p>
<ul>
<li>Model	    -       Train Recall	  -   Validation Recall	 - Overfit?</li>
</ul>
<hr/>
<ul>
<li>Decision Tree	 -  0.69	       -       0.68	      -         Good</li>
<li>Bagging      -    0.99         -      0.71        -         Overfit</li>
<li>Random Forest	-   1            -      0.68        -         Overfit</li>
<li>AdaBoost	    -   0.72	       -       0.73	      -         Good</li>
<li>Gradient Boost	- 0.74	       -       0.73	      -         Good</li>
<li>XGBoost	       -  0.89	       -       0.68	      -         Slight overfit</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=GBbub2T9Yl6X">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<ul>
<li><p>Based on the above undersampled recall scores, the training data and validation data recall scores matches very closely for Decision Tree, Ada Boosting and Gradient Boosting.</p>
</li>
<li><p>Hence selecting Decision Tree, Ada Boosting and Gradient Boosting for hypertuning</p>
</li>
</ul>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="jp-Cell jp-MarkdownCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=IKKk2b9wZ5_-">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<p>Using RandomizedSearchCV for hypertuning</p>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h4 id="Hypertuning-with-Decision-Tree-Classifier">Hypertuning with Decision Tree Classifier<a class="anchor-link" href="#Hypertuning-with-Decision-Tree-Classifier">¶</a></h4>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=jYiaUm-UCB_y">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [342]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%%time</span>

<span class="c1"># Choose the type of classifier.</span>
<span class="n">rf2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DecisionTreeClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Grid of parameters to choose from</span>
<span class="n">parameters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s1">'max_depth'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">7</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">15</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'min_samples_split'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'min_samples_leaf'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">8</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'max_features'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'sqrt'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'log2'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'criterion'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'gini'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'entropy'</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'splitter'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'best'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'random'</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="c1"># Type of scoring used to compare parameter combinations</span>
<span class="n">acc_scorer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">metrics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">make_scorer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metrics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">recall_score</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Run the random search</span>
<span class="n">grid_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">RandomizedSearchCV</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">rf2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">n_iter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">scoring</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">acc_scorer</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">cv</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">random_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">n_jobs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">verbose</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># using n_iter = 30, so randomized search will try 30 different combinations of hyperparameters</span>
<span class="c1"># by default, n_iter = 10</span>

<span class="n">grid_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">grid_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Print the best combination of parameters</span>
<span class="n">grid_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params_</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

 <span class="n">splitter</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'random'</span><span class="p">,</span>

<h4 id="Hypertuning-with-Ada-boosting">Hypertuning with Ada boosting<a class="anchor-link" href="#Hypertuning-with-Ada-boosting">¶</a></h4>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=iBG7pAsCfr6g">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [346]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%%time</span>

<span class="c1"># Choose the type of classifier.</span>
<span class="n">adaboost2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">AdaBoostClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Grid of parameters to choose from</span>
<span class="n">parameters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s1">'n_estimators'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">200</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">300</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">400</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'learning_rate'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mf">0.01</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.05</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span><span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'estimator'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span>
        <span class="n">DecisionTreeClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">),</span>  <span class="c1"># Decision stump</span>
        <span class="n">DecisionTreeClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">),</span>  <span class="c1"># Slightly deeper trees</span>
        <span class="n">DecisionTreeClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">)</span>   <span class="c1"># Deeper trees</span>
    <span class="p">],</span>
    <span class="s1">'algorithm'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'SAMME'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'SAMME.R'</span><span class="p">]</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="c1"># Type of scoring used to compare parameter combinations</span>
<span class="n">acc_scorer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">metrics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">make_scorer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metrics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">recall_score</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Run the random search</span>
<span class="n">grid_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">RandomizedSearchCV</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">adaboost2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">n_iter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">scoring</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">acc_scorer</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">cv</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">random_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">n_jobs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">verbose</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># using n_iter = 30, so randomized search will try 30 different combinations of hyperparameters</span>
<span class="c1"># by default, n_iter = 10</span>

<span class="n">grid_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">grid_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Print the best combination of parameters</span>
<span class="n">grid_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params_</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Set the clf to the best combination of parameters</span>
<span class="n">ada2_tuned</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">AdaBoostClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span>
 <span class="n">n_estimators</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">300</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">learning_rate</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">estimator</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">DecisionTreeClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">),</span>
 <span class="n">algorithm</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'SAMME'</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Fit the best algorithm to the data.</span>
<span class="n">ada2_tuned</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea"><div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">
</div><div class="jp-RenderedHTMLCommon jp-RenderedMarkdown jp-MarkdownOutput" data-mime-type="text/markdown">
<h4 id="Hypertuning-with-Gradient-boosting">Hypertuning with Gradient boosting<a class="anchor-link" href="#Hypertuning-with-Gradient-boosting">¶</a></h4>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div><div class="jp-Cell jp-CodeCell jp-Notebook-cell" id="cell-id=sqne8E9JjNwG">
<div class="jp-Cell-inputWrapper" tabindex="0">
<div class="jp-Collapser jp-InputCollapser jp-Cell-inputCollapser">
</div>
<div class="jp-InputArea jp-Cell-inputArea">
<div class="jp-InputPrompt jp-InputArea-prompt">In [350]:</div>
<div class="jp-CodeMirrorEditor jp-Editor jp-InputArea-editor" data-type="inline">
<div class="cm-editor cm-s-jupyter">
<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="o">%%time</span>

<span class="c1"># Choose the type of classifier.</span>
<span class="n">gboost2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">GradientBoostingClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">random_state</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Grid of parameters to choose from</span>
<span class="n">parameters</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">{</span>
    <span class="s1">'n_estimators'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">200</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">300</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">400</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Number of boosting stages</span>
    <span class="s1">'learning_rate'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mf">0.01</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.05</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Learning rate</span>
    <span class="s1">'max_depth'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">6</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">7</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Maximum depth of the trees</span>
    <span class="s1">'min_samples_split'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Min samples to split a node</span>
    <span class="s1">'min_samples_leaf'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">10</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Min samples at a leaf node</span>
    <span class="s1">'max_features'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'sqrt'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'log2'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="kc">None</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.3</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Max features for splitting nodes</span>
    <span class="s1">'subsample'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mf">0.5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.7</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">0.8</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="c1"># Fraction of samples used for fitting each tree</span>
    <span class="s1">'loss'</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="s1">'log_loss'</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="s1">'exponential'</span><span class="p">]</span>  <span class="c1"># Loss function to optimize</span>
<span class="p">}</span>

<span class="c1"># Type of scoring used to compare parameter combinations</span>
<span class="n">acc_scorer</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">metrics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">make_scorer</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">metrics</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">recall_score</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Run the random search</span>
<span class="n">grid_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">RandomizedSearchCV</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">gboost2</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">parameters</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">n_iter</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">30</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">scoring</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">acc_scorer</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="n">cv</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">random_state</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">n_jobs</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="o">-</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">verbose</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># using n_iter = 30, so randomized search will try 30 different combinations of hyperparameters</span>
<span class="c1"># by default, n_iter = 10</span>

<span class="n">grid_obj</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">grid_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">fit</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_train</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">y_train</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Print the best combination of parameters</span>
<span class="n">grid_obj</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">best_params_</span>
</pre></div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="c1"># Set the clf to the best combination of parameters</span>
<span class="n">gboost2_tuned</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">GradientBoostingClassifier</span><span class="p">(</span>
 <span class="n">subsample</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">1.0</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">n_estimators</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">50</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">min_samples_split</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">20</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">min_samples_leaf</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">max_features</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mf">0.1</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">max_depth</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">loss</span><span class="o">=</span> <span class="s1">'log_loss'</span><span class="p">,</span>
 <span class="n">learning_rate</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mf">1.0</span>
<span class="p">)</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">recall_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_test</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_test</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Checking precision score on test set</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Precision on test set"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">precision_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_test</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_test</span><span class="p">)))</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">""</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="c1"># Checking accuracy score on test set</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">"Accuracy on test set"</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">accuracy_score</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">y_test</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">model</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">predict</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">X_test</span><span class="p">)))</span>

<p>Based on the above scores below are the suggestions on using the model</p>
<ol>
<li>Recall:
AdaBoost has the highest recall (0.5165), which means it correctly identifies more positive cases compared to the other two models.</li>
</ol>
<p>Decision Tree has a recall of 0.4970, which is slightly lower, but still better than Gradient Boosting (0.5136).</p>
<ol start="2">
<li>Precision:
Decision Tree has the highest precision (0.6643), meaning it makes fewer mistakes in predicting positive cases than the other models.</li>
</ol>
<p>AdaBoost follows closely with 0.6493, and Gradient Boosting has the lowest precision (0.6163).</p>
<ol start="3">
<li>Accuracy:
Decision Tree has the highest accuracy (0.7496), meaning it's correctly classifying the most instances overall (both positives and negatives).</li>
</ol>
<p>AdaBoost and Gradient Boosting are very close in accuracy, with AdaBoost slightly outperforming Gradient Boosting.</p>
